                           <locus target="#53vb">Fol. 53vb</locus>: Inventory of the books of the church Mädḫane ʿAläm.  <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in a recent crude hand.
The books in the possession of Mädḫane ʿAläm church of ʿAddigrat are listed.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#172rb">Fol. 172rb</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 172rb: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘተሳየጦ፡ በንዋዩ፡ ሹም፡ አጋሜ፡ ካሳ፡ ወልዱ፡ ለቡርክ[sic]፡ ራስ፡ ሰብሐት፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለታቦተ፡ መድኃኔ፡ ዓለም፡ አድግራት፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሀ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in a well-trained hand, in red ink.
The note states that šum ʾagame Kasa (in office 1914-18, 1941-48), the son of ras Sǝbḥat (b. 1844, d. 1914), donated this book to the church Mädḫane ʿAläm in ʿAddigrat.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Two notes, almost completely erased and illegible, written in red ink: fols. 53va, 111vab.&#xD;
- Crude pencil notes: fols. 172rc, 173vc.&#xD;
- Erased passages: fols. 31rab, 100rc.&#xD;
- A number of interlinear addition and/or corrections: e.g., fols. 28va, 32vc, 38vb, 39rb.</item>
                     </list>
